The Lewis House built in 1899 is an historic Classical Revival house located at 1002 3rd Avenue, South in Fargo, North Dakota. On October 18, 1979, it was listed on the National Register of Historic Places. As of that date, it was the Minn-Kota Red Cross Chapter Office. Today, though, the Red Cross Chapter office is located at 2602 12th Street, North in Fargo.

